name: Sap Business One
description: Add a SAP Business One Element. This Works with SQL Server and Hana. You have to contact Cloud Elements support for Installation Directions at support@cloud-elements.com

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Event poller refresh interval
configuration.description: Set time interval for polling application (in minutes)

configuration.name: Event Poller Resources Configuration
configuration.description: Event Poller Resources Configuration. The configuration is defined via JSON

resources.description: Find Changes in the Finance System, using the provided CEQL search expression

parameters.name: objectName
parameters.description: The object name for which you want the changes

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: Only lastModifiedDate is supported for the changes query. eg where lastModifiedDate >= '2017-10-28'

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: Next Page link. You can get this from the Header of the previous search

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 10 if not supplied

resources.description: Find Customers in the Finance System, using the provided CEQL search expression

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. The where clause can include any field returned in the payload

parameters.name: nextPage
parameters.description: Next Page link. You can get this from the Header of the previous search

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

resources.description: Create a Customer in the Finance system.  Customer creation will flow through Cloud Elements to the Finance Service.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description:
The Customer object to be created.
field, the required fields indicated in the 'Customer' model are those required to create a new customer

resources.description: Delete a customer associated with a given ID from the Finance system. This marks the customer as inactive.  Specifying a Customer associated with a given ID that does not exist will result in an error message.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the customer to delete in the Finance system.

resources.description: Retrieve a Customer associated with a given ID from the Finance system. Specifying a Customer with an associated ID that does not exist will result in an error response.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The Id of the customer to retrieve from the finance system.

resources.description: Update a Customer given a set of partial attributes associated with a given Id (CardCode)

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the customer to update in the Finance system.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: The customer object, with those fields that are to be updated.
